# k8s-sage SLM — llama.cpp serving configuration
#
# This file documents the model parameters for serving via llama.cpp.
# Use run_llama_cpp.sh to launch the server.
#
# Model: k8s-sage fine-tuned Jamba 3B (GGUF Q4_K_M)
# Context: 1024 tokens (sufficient for single workload analysis)
# Threads: 2 (minimal CPU footprint in-cluster)

# Model parameters
MODEL /models/k8s-sage-q4.gguf

PARAMETER temperature 0.1
PARAMETER top_p 0.9
PARAMETER num_predict 512
PARAMETER stop <|end|>
PARAMETER stop </s>
PARAMETER stop <|im_end|>

SYSTEM """You are k8s-sage, a Kubernetes resource efficiency specialist. Analyse workload metrics and provide structured right-sizing recommendations. Always respond with valid JSON containing: cpu_request, cpu_limit, memory_request, memory_limit, pattern, confidence, reasoning_code, explanation, and risk fields."""
